84. Write a Java program to take the last three characters from a given string and add the three characters at both the front and back of the string. 
String length must be greater than three and more. (Must state)

import java.util.Arrays;

//<OWN METHOD>
public class w3 {
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        String str = "Python";
        String last3Char = str.substring(str.length()-3);
        System.out.println(last3Char + str + last3Char);
    }
}

